article.description: Matt Lewis had 21 points as James Madison ended its seven-game losing streak, topping UNC Wilmington 83-66 on Saturday.
article.headline: James Madison snaps losing streak, tops UNC Wilmington 83-66
article.linkText: James Madison snaps losing streak, tops UNC Wilmington 83-66
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. -- Matt Lewis had 21 points as James Madison ended its seven-game losing streak, topping UNC Wilmington 83-66 on Saturday. Dwight Wilson had 16 points and 12 rebounds for James Madison (9-13, 2-9 Colonial Athletic Conference), which forced a season-high 21 turnovers. Darius Banks added 13 points and Julien Wooden 11. Mike Okauru scored a career-high 22 points and had seven rebounds for the Seahawks (7-17, 2-9). Jaylen Sims added 11 points and six rebounds. Ty Gadsden had 10 points. The Dukes improve to 2-0 against the Seahawks on the season. James Madison defeated UNC Wilmington 64-60 on Jan. 2. James Madison matches up against Drexel on the road on Thursday. UNC Wilmington takes on Elon at home on Thursday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
